descr: "A value set specifies a set of codes drawn from one or more code systems."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a ValueSet resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this value set when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this value set is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the value set. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: identifier
fields.descr: "A formal identifier that is used to identify this value set when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance."

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the value set when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the value set author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence."

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the value set. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: title
fields.descr: "A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the value set."

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this value set. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this value set is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the value set was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the value set changes. (e.g. the 'content logical definition')."

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the value set."

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the value set from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate value set instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the value set is intended to be used."

fields.name: immutable
fields.descr: "If this is set to 'true', then no new versions of the content logical definition can be created.  Note: Other metadata might still change."

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this value set is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: copyright
fields.descr: "A copyright statement relating to the value set and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the value set."

fields.name: extensible
fields.descr: "Whether this is intended to be used with an extensible binding or not."

fields.name: compose
fields.descr: "A set of criteria that define the content logical definition of the value set by including or excluding codes from outside this value set. This I also known as the \"Content Logical Definition\" (CLD)."

fields.name: expansion
fields.descr: "A value set can also be \"expanded\", where the value set is turned into a simple collection of enumerated codes. This element holds the expansion, if it has been performed."

fields.name: text
fields.descr:
"A human-readable narrative that contains a summary of the resource, and may be used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it \"clinically safe\" for a human to just read the narrative. Resource definitions may define what content should be represented in the narrative to ensure clinical safety."
